          <div class="region">
           <a id="main-content">
           </a>
           <h1 class="page-header">
            Office of Disability Services
           </h1>
           <article class="node node-page clearfix" id="node-78">
            <header>
            </header>
            <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden">
             <div class="field-items">
              <div class="field-item even">
               <div>
                <div class="nH V8djrc byY">
                 <div class="nH">
                  <div class="ha">
                   <h2 style="text-align:center">
                    Got Scholarship?
                   </h2>
                   <p style="text-align:center">
                    <strong>
                     You might qualify for one or more University scholarships for students with disabilities!
                    </strong>
                    <br/>
                    To apply, visit the
                    <strong>
                     <a href="https://scholarships.uncc.edu/">
                      NinerScholars Portal
                     </a>
                    </strong>
                    . Learn more about
                    <a href="https://ds.uncc.edu/about-us/scholarships">
                     scholarships for students registered with Disability Services
                    </a>
                    .
                    <br/>
                    <strong>
                     <span>
                      DEADLINE EXTENDED! Complete scholarship applications are due online by April 1, 2019!
                     </span>
                    </strong>
                   </p>
                   <h2 style="text-align:center">
                    <span>
                    </span>
                    Disability Services New Online System for Students and Faculty
                   </h2>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                </div>
               </div>
               <p style="text-align:center">
                We are excited to offer an online system for students, faculty, and volunteer note takers! The system is called DS Portal.
                <br/>
                <strong>
                 Click the
                 <a href="https://ds.uncc.edu/ds-portal">
                  DS Portal
                 </a>
                 tab in the menu bar above for more information and links to the online system.
                </strong>
               </p>
               <p>
               </p>
               <hr/>
               <h2>
                Welcome!
               </h2>
               <h3>
                Our Mission
               </h3>
               <p>
                <strong>
                 The Office of Disability Services works to ensure that students with disabilities have access to education and campus life at UNC Charlotte. Through collaboration with the institution’s diverse community, Disability Services facilitates accommodations, discourse, and engagement to promote a universally accessible learning environment for all.
                </strong>
               </p>
               <h3>
                Important Dates
                <strong>
                 ​
                </strong>
               </h3>
               <ul>
                <li>
                 <strong>
                  January 16:
                 </strong>
                 <ul>
                  <li>
                   Last day to Add/Drop a course with No Grade
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   Last day to submit a
                   <a href="https://ninercentral.uncc.edu/grades-transcripts-graduation/grade-replacement">
                    Grade Replacement Request
                   </a>
                  </li>
                 </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                 <strong>
                  January 21:
                 </strong>
                 Martin Luther King Day - University closed
                </li>
                <li>
                 <strong>
                  March 4-8
                 </strong>
                 : Spring Break - No Classes
                </li>
                <li>
                 <strong>
                  March 19:
                 </strong>
                 Last day to withdraw from course(s); Grade subject to
                 <a href="https://provost.uncc.edu/policies-procedures/academic-policies-and-procedures/withdrawal-and-cancellation-enrollment-policy">
                  Withdrawal Policy
                 </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                 <strong>
                  April 15:
                 </strong>
                 Last day to schedule your finals in the DS Test Center
                </li>
               </ul>
               <h3>
                Requesting Accommodations
               </h3>
               <p>
                UNC Charlotte students who need accommodations should
                <a href="http://ds.uncc.edu/students/how-register-services">
                 register with Disability Services
                </a>
                .
                <strong>
                 To register with Disability Services (DS), students first need to submit appropriate documentation of their disability for review.
                </strong>
               </p>
               <ul>
                <li>
                 Most students will need their treating health care provider to complete the
                 <a href="/sites/ds.uncc.edu/files/media/DS%20Documentation%20Form%2010-2018.pdf">
                  Disability Documentation Form
                 </a>
                 .
                </li>
                <li>
                 Students with learning disabilities will need to submit their most recent full-scale psycho-educational documentation supporting their diagnosis.
                </li>
                <li>
                 Students requesting housing accommodations need their treating health care provider to complete
                 <em>
                  both
                 </em>
                 the
                 <a href="/sites/ds.uncc.edu/files/media/DS%20Documentation%20Form%2010-2018.pdf">
                  Disability Documentation Form
                 </a>
                 <span>
                 </span>
                 and the
                 <a href="/sites/ds.uncc.edu/files/media/Housing%20%26%20Meal%20Plan%20Addendum%202018.pdf">
                  Housing and Meal Plan Addendum
                 </a>
                 .
                </li>
               </ul>
               <p>
                Contact Disability Services with any questions about documentation or registering for services: 704-687-0040 or disability@uncc.edu.
               </p>
               <p>
                <strong>
                 Documentation may be submitted in the following ways:
                </strong>
               </p>
               <ul>
                <li>
                 In person, by visiting DS in Fretwell 230
                </li>
                <li>
                 By fax: 704-687-1395
                </li>
                <li>
                 By email: disability@uncc.edu
                </li>
                <li>
                 By mail: Office of Disability Services, Fretwell 230, UNC Charlotte, Charlotte, NC 28223
                </li>
               </ul>
               <h3>
                Access for Visitors and Students at Public Campus Events
               </h3>
               <p>
                Students or visitors to campus who need accommodations for a public campus event should contact Disability Services at 704-687-0040 or
                <a href="mailto:disability@uncc.edu">
                 disability@uncc.edu
                </a>
                . For more information, visit
                <a href="http://accessibility.uncc.edu/webforms/requesting-services-events">
                 UNC Charlotte's Accessibility website
                </a>
                .
               </p>
               <h3>
                Disability Services Office Hours
               </h3>
               <p>
                <strong>
                 Mon. - Fri. 8:00 am - 5:00 pm | Fretwell 230
                </strong>
               </p>
              </div>
             </div>
